node.name: Sleeping Dragon Corn Maze, Entrance
node.description: The entrance to the corn maze sits on a small hill, surrounded by a two-plank wooden fence. Songbirds regularly perch upon it, lending song to the air with their calls. The ripening harvest stretches as far as the eye can see, a labrynthine path carved through it that resembles the shape of an enormous dragon curled up to rest.

node.name: Corn Maze, Entrance
node.description: Tall stalks of ripe corn tower high on either side of the thoroughfare that winds through the field, forming a thick, dense maze. The leaves and branches bend inward and almost meet overhead, giving the maze an almost claustrophobic feel. Dry, almost dusty dirt lies bare in neat, even spaces between the ripening rows, which have changed from a green to a nearly golden color.

node.name: Corn Maze, Green Growth
node.description: Deep green stalks of corn rise in every direction, making it difficult to determine any clear path forward or backward. The space between the rows is fairly wide, and some entrepreneurial grass and weeds grow in between the towering stalks of corn. Insects buzz among the hardy plants that cover the thoroughfare.

Dark stalks of corn rise in every direction, making it very difficult to determine any clear path in the darkness. The space between the rows is fairly wide, and the ground is rather soft from the undergrowth between the towering stalks of corn. Crickets constantly chirp, their symphony filling the nighttime air with a cacophonous chorus.

node.name: Corn Maze, Dragon's Back
node.description: The tops of the corn stalks in this area bend toward each other, creating more of a tunnel through the maze than a clear path. Loose corn silks are strewn over the plants, and bare patches show where a few ears have already been plucked. Thickly clustered plants almost ready to harvest grow tall enough to obscure the view, making it difficult to get any bearings.
The tops of the corn stalks in this area bend toward each other, and bare patches show where a few ears have been plucked.

The tops of the corn plants in this area bend toward each other, blocking out almost all of the already dim nighttime light. A few glowbugs dance among the crop, drawn to a few puddles of water between the heavy plants. Few and far between, the clouds of insects provide just enough light to keep travelers from blundering into the thick walls.
A few glowbugs dance among the corn stalks, providing a wan light.

node.description: Large stones frame the little pond, which is surrounded on all sides by the wafting corn. The still water is rather clean and a couple feet deep, and several insects skate along its surface. A small steel pipe is visible at one end of the pool, which appears to be the source of the body of water.

node.name: Corn Maze, Dragon's Tail

node.description: A peaceful valley, sheltered by the surrounding hills, is laid out before you like a patchwork quilt of flowery meadows and neatly arranged farmland. Centered in this multicolored vista is a small village. You pause on the hilltop to enjoy this delightful view. A meadowlark circles overhead for a moment, warbling its song to you, before swooping down toward the village, following the line of a well-traveled road.

The moonlight reveals a small valley stretched out between the surrounding hills. You can see a multitude of tiny lamplights twinkling in the darkness below, and faroff sounds of laughter and singing hover in the sweet evening air. The faint outline of a road descends down into the night-cloaked valley.

node.name: Corn Maze, Exit
node.description: The corn in this section of the cornfield seems sad and withered, with both the leaves and the stalks almost fully yellowed with only occasional streaks of green within them. A large portion of the crop is partially bent over, tangled up with each other and unfit for both harvesting and consumption. A large swath of corn is cut out of the field in a jagged line, likely to separate the diseased corner of the field from the otherwise healthy harvest.
